Description: Shell of the Mediterranean marine 'Trochus Turbinatus' gastropod mollusc.
Curator's comments: Found in box of unregistered shells with other shells that had handwritten slips written by Petrie identifying the shell species and naming Naukratis as the provenance. This shell was found with a note by Petrie: 'Trochus Turbinatus medit. Mound of Gaief (Naucratis) in lowest strata'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (WC.32)
